Sentencas: The Fe-Ni-O system designed for producing bimetal-containing composite anodes of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was studied.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The solubility of nickel in the structure of spinel (Fe,Ni)(3)O-4 +/- delta at atmospheric oxygen pressure is similar to 1/3.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Moderate reduction at 1023 K and p(O-2) approximate to 10(-20) atm leads to partial decomposition of spinels, forming an electron-conducting phase (Fe,Ni)(1) (-) O-y and submicron bimetallic Fe-Ni particles on the oxide surface, which have potentially high catalytic activity.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electron conductivity has a thermally activated character and increases substantially during the reduction.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In the anode conditions of SOFCs, the electric conductivity reaches 30-100 S/cm, while the thermal expansion coefficients are similar to 12 x 10(-6) K-1, which ensures compatibility with solid electrolytes.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: At the same time, significant volume changes during the redox cycling (up to similar to 1% on the linear scale) necessitate the introduction of additional components such as yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ).
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the model composite anode of reduced Fe2NiO4 +/- delta and YSZ deposited on the YSZ solid electrolyte membrane was similar to 1.8 Ohm cm(2) at 923 K in a 4% H2-Ar-H2O atmosphere.
Titulo: Redox Behavior and Transport Properties of Composites Based on (Fe,Ni)3O4 ± δ for Anodes of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
